
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [yield] slot to return a set of values related to the server and request context. It retrieves the server's IP address using [server.ip], the request's IP address using [request.ip], and the host name associated with the request using [request.host], packaging these into a response.
yield
   server-ip:x:@server.ip
   request-ip:x:@request.ip
   host:x:@request.host
